cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper analyzes the popularity dynamics of social media, specifically YouTube, which involves the use of information retrieval techniques, multimedia analysis, and social network analysis. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Among these, cs.SI and cs.IR are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the study of social media popularity dynamics and the analysis of referrers that lead users to videos. The other categories are also relevant as they involve the analysis of multimedia content and user behavior, which are important factors in understanding popularity dynamics.
